02/09/2010
NEW YORK, United States -- Turkey took over the month-long rotating presidency of the UN Security Council on Wednesday (September 1st).
The previous holder was Russia.
On September 23rd, Turkish President Abdullah Gul will chair a meeting on peace protection.
Four days later, Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu will chair one on fighting terrorism.
Turkey joined the UN Security Council as a non-permanent member last year.
(DPA, World Bulletin - 01/09/10)
